Titolo: Digimon Rumble Arena

Anno: 2001

Descrizione: Digimon Rumble Arena is a fighting video game developed and published by Bandai in association with Hudson Soft for the PlayStation. It was released in Japan in 2001 and in North America and Europe the following year. Digimon Rumble Arena is part of a video games series connected to the Digimon franchise, and showcases the titular creatures within the context of a fighting video game. The player controls one of several Digimon and engages in combat with other Digimon within a variety of settings. Apart from the central fighting gameplay, a trio of mini-games are available upon the single-player campaign's completion. Digimon Rumble Arena received mixed reviews from critics, who underlined the game's resemblance to Super Smash Bros.. A sequel, Digimon Rumble Arena 2, was released in 2004 for the PlayStation 2, GameCube, and Xbox. A spiritual successor to the first two installments, Digimon All-Star Rumble, was released in 2014.



Genere: Fighting 

Valutazione: 65
